commText: de Kock and Rahul are at the crease. de Kock is on strike. Sam Curran will open the attack
Sam Curran to de Kock, no run, short of a good length and angling back into the left-hander, cramped de Kock for room whose dab results in an inside edge onto his body
Sam Curran to de Kock, no run, on a good length and in that channel just outside off, de Kock covers the line, lifts his bat and lets it go
Sam Curran to de Kock, no run, tad fuller ad just outside off - de Kock gets right behind the line on the defensive push to mid-on

Sam Curran to de Kock, FOUR, beautifully played, hint of swing on this awayswinger, but de Kock has it covered - presents the full face of the bat and then drives it straight of mid-off for a boundary
Sam Curran to de Kock, 1 run, Curran drags the length back on off, nudged wide of mid-wicket for a single
A slip for Rahul
Sam Curran to Rahul, no run, short of a good length and just outside off - Rahul gets besides the line and defends it to the off-side
Arshdeep Singh, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Arshdeep Singh to de Kock, 1 run, uppish and safe - on a good length and swinging away from the left-hander, de Kock wasn't in control as he reached out on the drive, sliced it in the air and to the right of cover-point
Arshdeep Singh to Rahul, wide, Arshdeep attempts the inswinger and spills it down leg, called as a wide
Arshdeep Singh to Rahul, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off - Rahul looks to drive and inner halves it past square leg, just a single
Arshdeep Singh to de Kock, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, driven straight to the fielder at mid-off
Arshdeep Singh to de Kock, 1 run, back of a length and just outside off - de Kock backs away slightly and then steers it backward of square on the off-side for a single
Arshdeep Singh to Rahul, 1 run, length ball at the pads, flicked down to long leg for a single

Arshdeep Singh to de Kock, 2 runs, fuller length delivery and well wide of off, de Kock throws his hands on the drive and gets a thick edge, flies towards the third man ropes and is well stopped by the fielder getting across, keeps them down to a couple
Kagiso Rabada, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Rabada to Rahul, 1 run, almost a screamer from Harshal Patel - ran a long way from long leg, dived forward and got both hands, but as he hit the ground, the ball popped out - back of a length and at the hips, Rahul wasn't in control as he played the flick behind square on the on-side
Rabada to de Kock, no run, short of a good length and angling back into the left-hander - de Kock went hard on the pull and mistimes it to the on-side
Rabada to de Kock, FOUR, slapped, width on offer from Rabada, de Kock gets on top of the bounce and then crunches it past point, races away to the ropes

Rabada to de Kock, SIX, lovely, he's off to a flier here, fuller length delivery and just outside off - de Kock waits on it, opens the face of the bat at the last moment, brings his wrists into play and then slices it over deep point for a maximum
Rabada to de Kock, no run, on a good length and just outside off, de Kock leans across and pushes it to the on-side
Rabada to de Kock, no run, that's an excellent comeback from Rabada - shortened the length and got it to jag back into the left-hander, cut de Kock in half and zipped past the inside edge
Arshdeep Singh to Rahul, SIX, cracking shot, pitched up by Arshdeep, right in the slot - high elbow and a straight bat as Rahul lofted it over mid-off, went sailing over the ropes for a maximum
Arshdeep Singh to Rahul, no run, banged in short and angling across the right-hander - Rahul swivels across on the pull, hit it flat and on the bounce to mid-on
Arshdeep Singh to Rahul, FOUR, this is good aggressive cricket from Rahul - pitched up by Arshdeep, he leans forward and lifts it nonchalantly over the b owler's head, one bounce and over the ropes

Arshdeep Singh to Rahul, 2 runs, sublime, tad too full and just outside off - Rahul lets the ball come and then brings the wrists into play, whipping it over mid-wicket, the ball plugs in the outfield and he's back for the second
Looks like Liam Livingstone has pulled his hamstring as he moved across to his left from the deep, he doesn't look too happy and walks away. This could be a big blow for the Kings
Arshdeep Singh to Rahul, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Arshdeep Singh to Rahul, out Caught by Bairstow!! But this is a big wicket now - KL was looking extremely dangerous and Arshdeep has sent him packing - back of a length and angled across the right-hander, Rahul was looking to use the pace and run it backward of point, but he doesn't bother to keep it down and is smartly caught by Bairstow, moving swiftly to his left at backward point. Rahul c Bairstow b Arshdeep Singh 15(9) [4s-1 6s-1]
Devdutt Padikkal, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Arshdeep Singh to Padikkal, no run, on a good length and just outside off, Padikkal gets well forward on the defensive push
Rabada to de Kock, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, sliced over backward point for a single
Rabada to Padikkal, FOUR, beautifully played, on a good length and well wide of off - Padikkal stands tall and then lifts it over mid-off, bounces away to the ropes in a hurry

Rabada to Padikkal, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Padikkal - short of a good length and just outside off, he lets the ball come, uses the pace, opens the face of the bat and then runs it past short third man
Rabada to Padikkal, no run, fuller length delivery on the pads, Padikkal shuffled across on the flick and missed, off the pad and rolled to the on-side
Rabada to Padikkal, 1 run, Rabada keeps it full and wide of off, a thick edge on the slice and the ball bounces in front of Harshal Patel at deep backward point
Rabada to de Kock, no run, Rabada shortens the length and gets it to straighten onto the left-hander - de Kock plays down the wrong line and is beaten

Highlights (Overs 1-5) -> de Kock opens his account with a lovely off-drive against Curran -> Harshal Patel puts down KL Rahul's catch at deep square leg -> Livingstone walks off the field due to an injury (3.4) -> Rahul perishes next ball as he is caught at backward point (3.5) -> Padikkal gets going with back-to-back boundaries against Rabada
Change of ends for Sam Curran
Sam Curran [1.0-0-5-0] is back into the attack
Sam Curran to Padikkal, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Sam Curran to Padikkal, out Caught by Dhawan!! . and he strikes immediately - Padikkal hangs his head back in disappointment as he walks off - back of a length and just outside off, the left-hander backed away and was looking to flat-bat it over mid-off's head, but he's hit it flat and down Dhawan's throat, a simple catch for the Punjab skipper and they've their second wicket now. Padikkal c Dhawan b Sam Curran 9(6) [4s-2]
Marcus Stoinis, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Sam Curran to Stoinis, 1 run, on a good length and at the pads, tucked in front of square on the on-side for a single
Sam Curran to de Kock, no run, short of a good length and just outside off - steered with an angled bat and straight to the fielder at short third man

Sam Curran to de Kock, 2 runs, that's slugged and de Kock has got enough to beat Harshal at mid-on - short of a good length and just outside off, was the slower ball and de Kock didn't read the change of pace, went through with the pull and miscued it over mid-on's head
Sam Curran to de Kock, no run, another slower ball outside off - de Kock swings hard and is undone by the change of pace, bounces through to the keeper

Sam Curran to de Kock, SIX, that's a proper slog - on a length and at the stumps, de Kock picked the length early, swivelled across and then thumped it over square leg, sending it sailing over the ropes
Time for spin and it's Rahul Chahar
Rahul Chahar, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Stoinis, 1 run, the leg-break, but it's dropped short and it's punched square past cover-point for a single
Rahul Chahar to de Kock, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle, nudged wide of mid-wicket for a single
Rahul Chahar to Stoinis, 1 run, tossed up just outside off, cut away square on the off-side for a single
Rahul Chahar to de Kock, 1 run, Chahar tosses one on the leg-stump line, tucked wide of mid-wicket for a single
Rahul Chahar to Stoinis, 1 run, pushed through on middle and leg, worked past square leg for a single
Rahul Chahar to de Kock, 2 runs, Chahar tosses one on middle, played with soft hands as de Kock knocked it wide of long-on, comes back for the second
Spin from both ends and it's Brar
Harpreet Brar, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Stoinis, no run, pushed through on off, Stoinis backs away and chops it to cover
Harpreet Brar to Stoinis, no run, dragged short and just outside off - crunched to the right of cover where Dhawan makes a smart stop, saved at least two runs there
Harpreet Brar to Stoinis, no run, pushed through flatter and on off, Stoinis slugs hard and mistimes it back at the bowler
Harpreet Brar to Stoinis, 2 runs, slower and wider of off, Stoinis waits and then drives, finding the gap to the left of cover and he's back for the second
Harpreet Brar to Stoinis, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, hacked down towards long-on, no timing and it's only a single
Harpreet Brar to de Kock, 1 run, Brar drifts one across the left-hander, hammered to deep cover for a single
Rahul Chahar to de Kock, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, tucked behind square on the on-side for a single
Rahul Chahar to Stoinis, SIX, beautifully played, tad too full from Chahar - right in the slot, Stoinis clears his front-leg and then hammers it back over the bowler's head for a maximum

Rahul Chahar to Stoinis, SIX, back-to-back sixes for Stoinis - Chahar dragged the length back, but it's tad too short, allows Stoinis to rock back and then hammer the pull over square leg, didn't get hold of the shot, but such is his power that the ball sailed away
Rahul Chahar to Stoinis, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Rahul Chahar to Stoinis, out Bowled!! Chahar has his man now and he's chuffed to bits - was pushed through flatter and quicker, skidded through and beat Stoinis's pull, smashing into the leg-stump and Stoinis's brief innings comes to an end. Was the attempted wrong 'un, think Stoinis picked it as he went back, but he's undone by the skiddy pace. Stoinis b Rahul Chahar 19(12) [6s-2]

They've taken the strategic break. LSG have scored at a healthy rate, but they've lost three wickets as well. Punjab keeping themselves interested with the wickets, but they'll be worried about Livingstone's injury
Marcus Stoinis vs Rahul Chahar in the IPL Runs: 78 Balls: 39 Dismissals: 2 Avg: 39 SR: 200 4s/6s: 3/8
Nicholas Pooran, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Rahul Chahar to Pooran, 1 run, tossed up on off, driven down to long-off for a single
Rahul Chahar to de Kock, 1 run, very full from Chahar, whipped down to long-on for a single
Harshal Patel, from round the wicket
Harshal Patel, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshal Patel to de Kock, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, chopped square on the off-side for a single
Back to over the wicket
Harshal Patel to Pooran, 1 run, short of a good length and on the pads, Pooran was looking to flick and gets an inside edge onto the pad, good diving stop at short fine
Back to over the wicket for de Kock
Harshal Patel to de Kock, 1 run, short of a good length and just outside off, cut square on the off-side for a single
Harshal Patel to Pooran, no run, fuller length delivery on off, driven back at the bowler
Harshal Patel to Pooran, 1 run, tad too full and at the pads, flicked past mid-wicket for a single
Harshal Patel to de Kock, FOUR, smashed, too short and too wide of off, de Kock brings the bottom hand into play as he drilled the drive wide of mid-off

Highlights (Overs 6-10) -> Curran removes Padikkal within the powerplay -> 50 up for LSG in the 6th over -> PBKS spinners bowl a couple of economical overs -> Stoinis is bowled by Chahar after conceding back-to-back sixes -> LSG - 88/3 at the halfway stage
Rabada back
Kagiso Rabada [2.0-0-21-0] is back into the attack
Rabada to Pooran, 1 run, back of a length and just outside off, Pooran runs it down towards third man for a single
Rabada to de Kock, FOUR, ugly and four, fuller length delivery outside off - de Kock threw himself on the slog, gets a big edge that went flying past the keeper, on the bounce and over the ropes
Rabada to de Kock, no run, back of a length and just outside off, steered straight to the fielder at backward point
Rabada to de Kock, 1 run, short of a good length and angling back into the left-hander, nudged behind square on the on-side for a single
Rabada to Pooran, no run, on a good length and just outside off, defended to the off-side
Rabada to Pooran, 1 run, tad fuller and arounde off, pushed into the gap square past point for a single
Rahul Chahar [2.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack

Rahul Chahar to Pooran, SIX, massive, Pooran loves taking on the spinners - flighted delivery on off and he's launched into the lofted drive, went vbery high and drops over the fielder's head at deep mid-wicket
Rahul Chahar to Pooran, FOUR, back-to-back boundaries for Pooran - dragged shorter and wider of off, he leans across and then hammers the drive wide of cover, giving the fielder at long-off no chance

Rahul Chahar to Pooran, SIX, thumped, this is turning out to be an expensive over - flighted delivery on off, Pooran gets forward and then lifts it nonchalantly over the bowler's head, sails over the sightscreen for another maximum
Rahul Chahar to Pooran, 2 runs, the wrong 'un, but the length is short and wide of off, clattered hard and to the right of cover - work for the fielder in the deep and Pooran's back for the second
Rahul Chahar to Pooran, 1 run, flatter and wider of off, pulled down to long-on for a single
Rahul Chahar to de Kock, 1 run, 20 off the over, flighted delivery on middle and leg, nudged wide of mid-wicket for a single
Harshal Patel [1.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack

Harshal Patel to de Kock, FOUR, cheeky and four, it's given as leg-byes though, but he's got a big under-edge onto the pad and the umpire missed it - shuffled right across on the lap and got a fine edge past short fine. The decision has been corrected and de Kock can celebrate his 21st IPL fifty
Harshal Patel to de Kock, wide, Harshal pushes one well wide of off and is called as a wide
Harshal Patel to de Kock, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, squirted to deep point on the drive
Harshal Patel to Pooran, 1 run, Harshal keeps it full and wide of off, driven to deep cover for a single
Harshal Patel to de Kock, 1 run, yorker length delivery on off, jammed in front of mid-off for a single
Harshal Patel to Pooran, byes, 1 run, change of pace from Harshal - slower ball pushed across the left-hander, Pooran slashes and misses, on the bounce to Jitesh Sharma who fumbles and allows a bye
Harshal Patel to de Kock, 1 run, the slower short ball, steered backward of square on the off-side for a single
They've taken the strategic break. 7 overs left and they've two well-set batters. LSG would be disappointed if they don't go past 190 from here
Arshdeep Singh [2.0-0-19-1] is back into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to de Kock, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Arshdeep Singh to de Kock, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! Top edgeeee and taken by the keeper running towards square leg. Short slower delivery, de Kock thought he could have the pull shot, big mishit and the keeper had ample time so he called for it to take a simple catch. The line was well wide of off and demanded an off-side shot, which QdK tells himself as he walks back. End of a handy good innings from de Kock. de Kock c Jitesh Sharma b Arshdeep Singh 54(38) [4s-5 6s-2]
Ayush Badoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Arshdeep Singh to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, short of length delivery outside off stump, Badoni dabs to third man
Arshdeep Singh to Pooran, FOUR, creamy cover drive! Full and outside off stump, Pooran leans forward and crashes the drive for four more. WIckets or not, he's not changing his approach
Arshdeep Singh to Pooran, FOUR, top edge over the keeper now. Pace on shortish delivery, Pooran looks to pull, gets a thick edge and it flies away for four more
Arshdeep Singh to Pooran, 1 run, low full toss, Pooran leans forward and drives to long-off
Arshdeep Singh to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, short and on the leg stump, Badoni gets inside the line and pulls to long leg
Quinton de Kock vs Arshdeep Singh in T20s Runs: 31 Balls: 32 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 10.33 SR: 96.87 Dots: 15
This is surely a 180-190 pitch without dew
Harpreet Brar [1.0-0-4-0] is back into the attack

Harpreet Brar to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, edge and put down. Tough for the keeper, huge deflection, those just stick. Slider outside off stump, Badoni looks to cut, thick edge and he escapes as Jitesh Sharma couldn't close his hands in time
Harpreet Brar to Pooran, 1 run, slogs and is rushed for pace by this quicker delivery, impact on leg stump, but difficult to get these LBWs with so much doubt of ball missing leg
Harpreet Brar to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, length delivery, Badoni works it to deep square leg
Harpreet Brar to Pooran, SIX, he couldn't slog from the crease previous ball he tried so used his feet to get to closer to the pitch of the ball and launches it over wide long-on
Harpreet Brar to Pooran, 1 run, mistimes the drive to long-on
Harpreet Brar to Ayush Badoni, no run, looks for a tap and run single, but defends it too hard towards cover

Highlights (Overs 11-15) -> 100 up for LSG in the 12th over -> Pooran takes on Chahar, the leggie concedes 20 runs in an over -> de Kock brings up his fifty with a cheeky boundary -> Arshdeep comes back to draw curtains to de Kock's knock -> Jitesh Sharma puts down Badoni's catch behind the wickets
Kagiso Rabada [3.0-0-28-0] is back into the attack
Rabada to Pooran, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Rabada to Pooran, out Bowled!! This is a big dent. Nic Pooran is fuming with himself for playing a poor shot and gifting his wicket. This was a length delivery that was acres outside off stump, just like QdK, demanded an off-side shot but Pooran gets sucked into a slog and he drags it onto the stumps. Shadow-practices the shot over cover as he walks back. This is surely going to makke a difference of at least 15 runs to the final total for LSG. He was looking absolutely set and dangerous. Pooran b Rabada 42(21) [4s-3 6s-3]
Krunal Pandya, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Rabada to Krunal Pandya, 2 runs, fullish delivery, Krunal drives through extra-cover, waits for the ball to pass the fielder and gets two
Rabada to Krunal Pandya, 2 runs, now a dab past backward point and it's in the gap for two more. Well done!

Rabada to Krunal Pandya, no run, off the pad and straight to backward point. Soft appeal for catch but there was no inside edge. Short of a length delivery angling in and beatng Krunal on the flick, flies off the thigh pad
Rabada to Krunal Pandya, SIX, oh he's managed to pull this despite not bouncing as expected. Short delivery that was only just above hip height, Krunal pulls and manages to middle it over square leg
Rabada to Krunal Pandya, leg byes, 1 run, fullish and angling in, Krunal works it to square leg
Pooran vs Rabada in the IPL Runs: 32 Balls: 25 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 10.67 SR: 128
Sam Curran [2.0-0-14-1] is back into the attack
Sam Curran to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, slower delivery on the stumps, Krunal works it to mid-wicket
Sam Curran to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, slower delivery down leg, Badoni works it to backward square leg
Sam Curran to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, short and rising, mistimed pull to deep square leg
Sam Curran to Ayush Badoni, no run, nice slower delivery, Badoni mistimes the drive back to the bowler as he was deceived by the lack of pace
Sam Curran to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, uppish but no one at mid-on or mid-wicket! Shortish slower delivery, Badoni mistimes the pull as he plays early, escapes
Sam Curran to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, goes for the yorker but bowls really full, digs it out uppishly to long-on
Harshal Patel [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, no run, pace on yorker, Krunal drives to mid-off

Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, FOUR, big slog, under edge escapes past the stumps for four. Good slower delivery that forced a false shot. Another slog attempted on the leg-side when the ball was miles outside off stump. Fine leg was in so the batter gets four
Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, 2 runs, full delivery, Krunal drills down the ground, mid-off dives to the left and cuts it off
Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, wide, oh pacy short delivery but that's too high says the ump
Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, FOUR, drilled away for four! Full and outside off stump as he misses the yorker, Krunal smacks it through cover and the deep point fielder had no chance
Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, wide, oh went for the leg stump yorker but fires down leg
Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, wide, goes for the wide yorker now and fires a low full toss outside off stump. Called a wide. Seemed 50-50 but need a replay

Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, SIX, oh that seemed like a check lofted shot! Oh yes, was slightly done in by the lack of pace, Krunal was ready for a lofted off-drive, was troubled a wee bit while connecting yet he managed to middle it well enough to clear the long-off ropes to the left of the fielder
Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, short and now pulled through backward square leg. 20 off that over and Krunal has ensured Pooran's absence isn't felt
Sam Curran to Krunal Pandya, FOUR, short and slow outside off stump, third man up so Krunal jumps and upper cuts over the fielder for a boundary. This is good batting and poor bowling
Sam Curran to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, short slower delivery, Krunal mistimes the pull to backward square leg
Sam Curran to Ayush Badoni, 2 runs, Badoni slogs now but toe-ends this length delivery wide of deep mid-wicket
Sam Curran to Ayush Badoni, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Sam Curran to Ayush Badoni, out Caught by Bairstow!! In the airrrr, straight to long-on. Back of the hand slower delivery int the slot for the tease, Badoni thought he could have a biggie, mistimed it completely and Jonny B didn't have to move much for a simple catch. Ayush Badoni c Bairstow b Sam Curran 8(10)
Ravi Bishnoi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Sam Curran to Ravi Bishnoi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Sam Curran to Ravi Bishnoi, out Caught by (sub)Thyagarajan!! This is again in the air and taken at deep backward square leg. Sam Curran is on a hat-trick now. He picked up a 3-fer last time here against LSG and he's done it again. Short slower delivery into the wicket, Bishnoi pulls, no power and holes out. Ravi Bishnoi c (sub)Thyagarajan b Sam Curran 0(1)
One ball left. Will he go for the toe-crusher against the tailender?
Mohsin Khan, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Sam Curran to Mohsin Khan, 2 runs, he does go for the blockhole but misses it, Mohsin goes for a big drive down the ground, manages to hit it wide of long-on for two. Krunal will face the next over
Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, no run, lovely low full toss, almost a yorker drilled to long-on but he won't take the run
Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, 2 runs, mistimed, in the air and safe at mid-off. Krunal looks to slog this low full toss over leg-side, toe-ends it completely

Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, FOUR, he was waiting for another blockhole ball and Harshal Patel gave him the low full toss. Krunal lofts the drive over the leaping man at cover and he's got the boundary needed
Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, out Mohsin Khan Run Out!! Moshin is runout as he had to sacrifice. Low full toss, Krunal smacks it down the ground, ball hits the stumps and almost stops. Mohsin Khan thought of stealing a run which wasn't on. Krunal rightly said let me have strike. Harshal collects the ball and ensures he removes a stump because the bails had already come off. Still a decent over from Harshal Patel - just six off it with two balls to go. Mohsin Khan run out (Harshal Patel) 2(1)
Impact sub on for LSG - KL out, Naveen in. Looks like some issue with the stumps not lighting up so small delay
Naveen-ul-Haq, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, no run, in the airrrr, low full toss mistimed to long-off. Jonny B dives forward but it doesn't carry. Krunal denies a single as he wants strike. Just 6 runs off 5 balls now

Harshal Patel to Krunal Pandya, 2 runs, another low full toss, slogged wide of long-on, easy two and they will finish with 199. Sam Curran fumbles but that doesn't cost any. Turns out to be a great final over from Harshal, gives his side some momentum going into the break

21:20 Local Time, 15:50 GMT, 21:20 IST: 199 is par with the pitch being very good for batting. LSG could have easily had 220+ though. KL and DDP threw it away at the start. QdK batted sensibly at the top but got to admire how LSG never took the foot off the pedal. Stoinis came in at No. 4 for a short intent-filled cameo and Pooran was always about intent. Took calculated risks to ensure the scoreboard was always moving. Badoni struggled and with Rabada getting Pooran with four odd overs to go it looked like PBKS could close this out very well but Krunal put on a brilliant display of finishing to give his bowlers a great chance. Curran used the cutters to great effect. Arshdeep got the key wickets of KL and QdK. Should dew not set in, LSG will really fancy their chances.

Krunal Pandya: I like to play situations, I am prepared that way, I am quite flexible, can bat anywhere from number 3 to number 7. Just want to go out there and contribute. I like to prepare, take cricket as an exam. Like to prepare, but the result is not in my hand. 199 is a good total, if we bowl smartly we can defend this. The surface has changed, much better than last year. Need to adapt to the conditions. Need to bowl accordingly and see how it goes.

PBKS bowling today Sam Curran and Harpreet Brar: 3/42 from 6 overs (ER: 7) Others: 4/155 from 14 overs (ER: 11.07) Highest first innings totals in IPL matches in Lucknow 199/8 - LSG vs PBKS, 2024 193/6 - LSG vs DC, 2023 177/3 - LSG vs MI, 2023 159/8 - LSG vs PBKS, 2023 135/6 - GT vs LSG, 2023 LSG’s 199/8 is the joint highest first innings total in 38 T20 matches in Lucknow, matching India’s 199/2 against Sri lanka in 2022. LSG have lost just two of the 14 completed matches while defending a score in the IPL: by five wickets against GT at the Wankhede in 2022 and by five wickets against PBKS in Lucknow last year, the latter being the highest successful chase at this venue in T20s (target: 160).

Highest 1st innings totals for LSG 257/5 vs PBKS, Mohali, 2023 210/0 vs KKR, Mumbai DYP, 2022 199/4 vs MI, Brabourne, 2022 199/8 vs PBKS, Lucknow, 2024 PBKS bowling in IPL 2024 Harpreet Brar: 3/41 from 9 overs (Avg: 13.66, ER: 4.55) Others: 17/491 from 50.2 overs (Avg: 28.88, ER: 9.76)

Out come the players for the second innings. Is Livingstone fit enough to bat? Spin bowling coach Sunil Joshi during a sideline interview earlier with the host broadcaster confirmed he was set to bowl today if not for the injury. PBKS will hope it's not too serious to rule him out of the game today.
Spin to start with
